 JOHANNESBURG - For years, the Johannesburg Roads Agency has been criticised for the state of the city's roads and infrastructure. eNCA is now in possession of a forensic report, revealing irregular expenditure of more than R400-million with officials allegedly grossly overcharging for certain projects but these officials are yet to be held to account. READ: Local Government | 'Let's get rid of corruption' - Ramaphosa The JRA board has told eNCA, the City’s forensic and investigation service has been tasked with speeding up the conclusion of all audit reports. Meanwhile, the Public Protector's office says the matter was once before them. eNCA Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more on this exclusive story in the video above.